    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-17T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-17T22:00:00-05:00" n="73"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.796/2–1848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-18T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 18, 1948—11 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 17—11:41 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>367. Since publicity might have unfortunate repercussions, Consulate General will
                    be discreet in disseminating information contained in last sentence Deptel 288,
                    February 16, unless further instructed by Department or Embassy.</p>
                <p>Sent Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
